ttribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Andrew Misplon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1531:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce Page Builder version <code>2.12.0</code> and Widgets Bundle version <code>1.18.0</code> introduced wide-ranging accessibility enhancements. Users can now tab through all Page Builder and Widgets Bundle views, form fields and settings, making changes as required without using a mouse. Keyboard navigation is now available in the following areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Page Builder rows, and columns.</li>\n<li>Page Builder Layouts view.</li>\n<li>Page Builder History view.</li>\n<li>Page Builder Live Editor.</li>\n<li>Page Builder row and widget form navigation.</li>\n<li>Widgets Bundle form field navigation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a semi-technical user and would like to view the work involved in these enhancements, please, find the pull request links below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Page Builder: <a href=\"https://github.com/siteorigin/siteorigin-panels/pull/772\">https://github.com/siteorigin/siteorigin-panels/pull/772</a></li>\n<li>Widgets Bundle: <a href=\"https://github.com/siteorigin/so-widgets-bundle/pull/1206\">https://github.com/siteorigin/so-widgets-bundle/pull/1206</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you or your organization make use of Page Builder or Widgets Bundle accessibility features and have any questions or requests, please, let us know. </p>\n<p>Thanks for reading.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com/page-builder-accessibility-enhancements/\">Page Builder Accessibility Enhancements</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com\">SiteOrigin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://siteorigin.com/page-builder-accessibility-enhancements/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"Widgets Bundle: WP Super Cache &amp; Swift Performance Enhancements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://siteorigin.com/widgets-bundle-wp-super-cache-swift-performance-enhancements/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://siteorigin.com/widgets-bundle-wp-super-cache-swift-performance-enhancements/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 03 Jun 2021 18:25:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://siteorigin.com/?p=313748\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:734:\"<p>The SiteOrigin Widgets Bundle version <code>1.20.0</code> introduces compatibility for <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WP Super Cache</a> and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/swift-performance-lite/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Swift Performance</a> plugins. The new compatibility ensures that WP Super Cache and Swift Performance won\'t reference outdated Widgets Bundle CSS files.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com/widgets-bundle-wp-super-cache-swift-performance-enhancements/\">Widgets Bundle: WP Super Cache &#038; Swift Performance Enhancements</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com\">SiteOrigin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Andrew Misplon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1712:\"<p>The SiteOrigin Widgets Bundle version <code>1.20.0</code> released on the 1st of June introduces compatibility for <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WP Super Cache</a> and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/swift-performance-lite/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Swift Performance</a> plugins. The new compatibility ensures that WP Super Cache and Swift Performance won&#8217;t reference outdated Widgets Bundle CSS files after a page containing SiteOrigin Widgets is saved. The Widgets Bundle along with all SiteOrigin plugins is actively developed on <a href=\"https://github.com/siteorigin/so-widgets-bundle\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a>. If you&#8217;re a technical user and would like to take a look at the commits that went into this improved caching plugin support, you can find the pull request <a href=\"https://github.com/siteorigin/so-widgets-bundle/pull/1258\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>As part of our ongoing efforts to offer the best possible plugin compatibility, the Widgets Bundle introduced Autoptimize plugin support in 2019, read more about that in the announcement <a href=\"https://siteorigin.com/boost-siteorigin-plugin-performance-autoptimize/\">Boost SiteOrigin Plugin Performance with Autoptimize</a>.</p>\n<p>Thanks for reading, if you have any questions or requests, please, let us know in the comments below.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com/widgets-bundle-wp-super-cache-swift-performance-enhancements/\">Widgets Bundle: WP Super Cache &#038; Swift Performance Enhancements</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://siteorigin.com\">SiteOrigin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://siteorigin.com/widgets-bundle-wp-super-cache-swift-performance-enhancements/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\